UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="wysiwyg prose line-clamp-14 overflow-hidden"><div><p><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><span style="font-family: arial,sans-serif;"> </span></span><!--StartFragment -->Step into the fast-paced world of tech with the ICT40120 Certificate IV in Information Technology—delivered as a dynamic traineeship that blends formal training with real-world experience. This nationally recognised qualification equips you with essential IT skills in networking, cybersecurity, support, and cloud technologies, while you earn and learn on the job.</p><p>The traineeship model offers a powerful advantage: you’ll apply what you learn in real time, gaining hands-on experience in a professional setting. This means you’re not just studying theory—you’re solving real problems, working with real systems, and contributing to your team from day one. You’ll build confidence, develop workplace-ready skills, and grow your professional network—all while being supported by experienced mentors and trainers.</p><p>Whether you're starting out or upskilling, this pathway sets you up for success in a rapidly evolving industry. By the end of the program, you’ll have both a qualification and practical experience that employers value—giving you a competitive edge in the job market.</p><p><strong>Learn. Earn. Grow.</strong> The ICT40120 Certificate IV in Information Technology Traineeship is your gateway to a rewarding career in tech.</p><p><!--EndFragment --></p></div><div><p><!--StartFragment -->As part of your study, students have the opportunity to pursue the following industry certifications at no additional cost, subject to student performance. These micro-accreditations are recognised by industry and can bolster your knowledge and skills even further for future employment.These certifications include: Amazon Cloud Foundations, CCNA: Introduction to Networks, CCNA: Switching, Routing, and Wireless Essentials, CCNA: Enterprise Networking, Security and Automation, Cisco 