UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="wysiwyg prose line-clamp-14 overflow-hidden"><div><p><!--StartFragment --></p><p>The 10890NAT - Certificate II in Learning an Australian First Nation's Language course is designed to enhance language learning opportunities within schools and communities. It aims to provide foundational skills in an Australian First Nation's language, fostering cultural identity and supporting further education and vocational pathways.</p><p>Delivery includes On-Country visits, residential workshops, and guest speakers, featuring Elders and respected persons. These elements will be developed in partnership, collaboration, and endorsement with Traditional Owner Groups, and overseen by the Statewide Governance structure. Delivery methods include both face-to-face and online formats, consisting of tutorials, tasks, breakout rooms, group work, hands-on experiences, and presentations.</p><p>The Certificate II focuses on developing foundational language skills, enhancing cultural understanding, and fostering community engagement. It supports further education and vocational pathways while strengthening cultural identity through the learning of an Australian First Nation's language.<!--EndFragment --></p></div><div><p><strong>Additional Federation TAFE entry requirement</strong></p><p>Eligible students must supply a letter of support from their Traditional Owner group stating which First Nations language the prospective student is linked to and are endorsed to study. </p><h3>IT requirements</h3><p>To do this course you’ll need a fast and reliable computer and access to high-speed internet. Expect to use about 5GB of data per month for every unit you’re doing. Find out more about the <a href="https://www.federation.edu.au/students/new-students/minimum-it-requirements/">minimum IT requirements</a> for studying with us.</p><h4>Got questions?</h4><p>Call us on 1800 333 864, start a live chat or <a href="https://www.federation.edu.au/contact/">submit an enquiry</a>.</p><h4>Student support</h4><p>The support we offer is second to none. Need academic help? No problem. Extra access or financial assistance? Let’s see what we can do. <a href="https://www.federation.edu.au/study/why-federation/support/">View our student services</a>.</p><h4>The fine print</h4><p>The commencement of all courses is subject to available funding and enrolment quotas.</p><p>Everything in this course overview is correct at the time of being published. However, the University reserves the right to alter any course, procedure or fee. Please check for changes before you apply or enrol.</p><p>Federation University uses Victorian and Commonwealth Government funding (for eligible students) to deliver training.</p><h4>School department</h4><p>Federation TAFE</p></div></div>',
