    course_description = '<div class="wysiwyg prose line-clamp-14 overflow-hidden"><div><p>Technical staff in full-time employment in the asset management field will enhance their skills in this course, which embraces leadership and management techniques, the organisation, planning and application of maintenance and maintenance strategies, terotechnological aspects of engineering economics and accountancy, and the implementation of maintenance planning systems, asset operations optimisation and more.</p><p>The knowledge achieved can be applied in fields such as manufacturing processes, transport, power generation and the efficient operation of industrial, commercial and civic buildings, with the goal of increasing industrial competitiveness and benefiting a company's bottom line.</p><p>To find out more, download our <a href="https://federation.edu.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0005/586184/Fed_MREng_4ppA4_web.pdf?_gl=1*1vl9m9f*_gcl_aw*R0NMLjE2ODA2Nzk2NTIuRUFJYUlRb2JDaE1Jb0llVnlwdVNfZ0lWMnNGTUFoMGdEUWthRUFBWUFTQUFFZ0lnS2ZEX0J3RQ..*_gcl_dc*R0NMLjE2ODA2Nzk2NTIuRUFJYUlRb2JDaE1Jb0llVnlwdVNfZ0lWMnNGTUFoMGdEUWthRUFBWUFTQUFFZ0lnS2ZEX0J3RQ..&amp;_ga=2.192650602.1919161047.1682210443-1722011824.1666668941">maintenance and reliability brochure</a>.</p></div><div><p>Benefit from our extensive experience in delivering off-campus courses to students across Australia and internationally. View our <a href="https://federation.edu.au/__data/assets/pdf_file/0005/586184/Fed_MREng_4ppA4_web.pdf?_gl=1*1vl9m9f*_gcl_aw*R0NMLjE2ODA2Nzk2NTIuRUFJYUlRb2JDaE1Jb0llVnlwdVNfZ0lWMnNGTUFoMGdEUWthRUFBWUFTQUFFZ0lnS2ZEX0J3RQ..*_gcl_dc*R0NMLjE2ODA2Nzk2NTIuRUFJYUlRb2JDaE1Jb0llVnlwdVNfZ0lWMnNGTUFoMGdEUWthRUFBWUFTQUFFZ0lnS2ZEX0J3RQ..&amp;_ga=2.192650602.1919161047.1682210443-1722011824.1666668941">Maintenance and Reliability Engineering brochure.</a></p><h4>Deferment of Admission</h4><p>Applicants are not permitted to defer admission into the course.</p><h3>IT requirements</h3><p>To do this course you’ll need a