UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="wysiwyg prose line-clamp-14 overflow-hidden"><div>LEA001 is a specialized unit designed to support students preparing for the Licensed Electrician's Assessment (LEA), which is a requirement for obtaining an Unrestricted Electrician's Licence in Victoria.<br/> <br/> Who It's For:<br/> - Students completing UEE30820.<br/> - Those applying for their electrical licence exam through ESV.<br/> - Typically offered to local students to reduce travel and improve work-life balance.<br/> <br/> What Students Can Expect to Achieve<br/> 1. Exam Readiness<br/> - Focused preparation for the LEA exams, including theory, practical, and regulatory components.<br/> - Access to sample papers and marking guides provided by ESV.<br/> 2. Regulatory Knowledge<br/> - Understanding of Electrical Regulatory Authority Council (ERAC) performance capabilities<br/> - Familiarity with licensing requirements, safety standards, and compliance regulations.<br/> 3. Practical Skills<br/> - Hands-on training in fault finding, installation, testing, and maintenance of electrical systems.<br/> - Reinforcement of skills learned in UEE30820 through targeted practice.<br/> 4. Local Study Benefits<br/> - Reduced travel time.<br/> - Improved balance between study, work, and personal life.<br/> - Supportive learning environment close to home.<br/> <br/> Licensed Electrical Assessment Training - LEA001 includes units:<br/> SWP001 Safe Working Practice<br/> LET001 Licenced Electricians Theory<br/> LEP001 Licenced Electricians Practical</div><div><h4>Got questions?</h4><p>Call us on 1800 333 864, start a live chat or <a href="https://www.federation.edu.au/contact/">submit an enquiry</a>.</p><h4>Student support</h4><p>The support we offer is second to none. Need academic help? No problem. Extra access or financial assistance? Let’s see what we can do. <a href="https://www.federation.edu.au/study/why-federation/support/">View our student services</a>.</p><h4>The fine print</h4><p